cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.GT, cs.CR

The paper discusses the technical and economic implications of resource sharing in millimeter wave networks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on cellular networks and the consideration of network simulations suggest that cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses information theory and communication technology, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communication and Networking). The consideration of market entry and strategic decisions suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
